question: What is the average fastest lap time of the top 10 drivers in the 2006 United States Grand Prix?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    AVG(
        CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 +
        CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) +
        CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000
    ) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM 
    races AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    results AS T2
ON 
    T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE 
    T1.year = 2006 
    AND T1.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
    AND T2.rank < 11;

SELECT AVG(results.fastestLapTime) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM results
INNER JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId
WHERE races.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND races.year = 2006
  AND results.rank < 11;

SELECT AVG(CAST(REPLACE(results.fastestLapTime, ':', '.') AS REAL)) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM results
INNER JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId
WHERE races.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND races.year = 2006
  AND results.rank < 11;

SELECT AVG(CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, -3), ':', '.') AS REAL)) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM races AS T1
INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE T1.year = 2006
  AND T1.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND T2.position <= 10;

SELECT AVG(CAST(SUBSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 +
            CAST(SUBSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1) AS REAL)) AS avg_fastest_lap_time
FROM results AS T1
INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE T2.year = 2006
  AND T2.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND T1.rank < 11;

SELECT 
    AVG(
        CAST(SUBSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 + 
        CAST(SUBSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1) AS REAL)
    ) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM 
    results AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    races AS T2 
ON 
    T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE 
    T2.year = 2006 
    AND T2.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
    AND T1.rank < 11;

SELECT AVG(
    CAST(SUBSTR(fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 +
    CAST(SUBSTR(fastestLapTime, INSTR(fastestLapTime, ':') + 1) AS REAL)
) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM results AS T2
INNER JOIN races AS T1 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE T1.year = 2006
  AND T1.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND T2.position < 11;

SELECT AVG(
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) * 60000 + -- Minutes to milliseconds
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 + -- Seconds to milliseconds
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') - 1) AS INTEGER) -- Fractional seconds to milliseconds
) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM races AS T1
INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
WHERE T1.year = 2006
  AND T1.name = 'United States Grand Prix'
  AND T2.rank < 11;

question: List down top 3 German drivers who has the shortest average pit stop duration and were born between 1980-1985.
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    d.forename || ' ' || d.surname AS fullName
FROM 
    drivers d
INNER JOIN 
    pitStops p
ON 
    d.driverId = p.driverId
WHERE 
    d.nationality = 'German'
    AND strftime('%Y', d.dob) BETWEEN '1980' AND '1985'
GROUP BY 
    d.driverId, d.forename, d.surname
ORDER BY 
    AVG(p.duration) ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    d.forename, 
    d.surname
FROM 
    drivers d
JOIN 
    pitStops p
ON 
    d.driverId = p.driverId
WHERE 
    d.nationality = 'German' 
    AND CAST(strftime('%Y', d.dob) AS INTEGER) BETWEEN 1980 AND 1985
GROUP BY 
    d.driverId
ORDER BY 
    AVG(CAST(p.duration AS REAL)) ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    d.forename, 
    d.surname, 
    AVG(p.duration) AS avg_pit_duration
FROM 
    drivers d
INNER JOIN 
    pitStops p
ON 
    d.driverId = p.driverId
WHERE 
    d.nationality = 'German'
    AND SUBSTR(d.dob, 1, 4) BETWEEN '1980' AND '1985'
GROUP BY 
    d.driverId
ORDER BY 
    avg_pit_duration ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    d.forename || ' ' || d.surname AS driver_name
FROM 
    drivers d
JOIN 
    pitStops p
ON 
    d.driverId = p.driverId
WHERE 
    d.nationality = 'German'
    AND d.dob BETWEEN '1980-01-01' AND '1985-12-31'
GROUP BY 
    d.driverId
ORDER BY 
    AVG(p.duration) ASC
LIMIT 3;

WHERE 
    PA.sprint_speed >= 97
    AND strftime('%Y', PA.date) BETWEEN '2013' AND '2015';

    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id

question: Who has the highest average finishing rate between the highest and shortest football player?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    P.player_name
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.height = (SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player) OR
    P.height = (SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player)
GROUP BY 
    P.player_name
ORDER BY 
    AVG(PA.finishing) DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the player with the highest average finishing rate
-- among the tallest and shortest players
WITH Heights AS (
    SELECT MAX(height) AS max_height, MIN(height) AS min_height
    FROM Player
),
FilteredPlayers AS (
    SELECT P.player_api_id, P.height
    FROM Player AS P
    INNER JOIN Heights AS H
    ON P.height = H.max_height OR P.height = H.min_height
)
SELECT PA.player_api_id, AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing
FROM Player_Attributes AS PA
INNER JOIN FilteredPlayers AS FP
ON PA.player_api_id = FP.player_api_id
GROUP BY PA.player_api_id
ORDER BY avg_finishing DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the player with the highest average finishing rate between the tallest and shortest players
SELECT P.player_name, AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing
FROM Player P
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes PA ON P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE P.height = (SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player)
   OR P.height = (SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player)
GROUP BY P.player_api_id, P.player_name
ORDER BY avg_finishing DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the player with the highest average finishing rate between the tallest and shortest players
WITH tallest_shortest_players AS (
    SELECT player_api_id
    FROM Player
    WHERE height = (SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player)
       OR height = (SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player)
),
player_finishing_rates AS (
    SELECT 
        P.player_name,
        AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing_rate
    FROM 
        Player AS P
    INNER JOIN 
        Player_Attributes AS PA
    ON 
        P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
    WHERE 
        P.player_api_id IN (SELECT player_api_id FROM tallest_shortest_players)
    GROUP BY 
        P.player_api_id, P.player_name
)
SELECT 
    player_name
FROM 
    player_finishing_rates
ORDER BY 
    avg_finishing_rate DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the player with the highest average finishing rate
-- among the tallest and shortest players
WITH HeightRange AS (
    SELECT
        MAX(height) AS max_height,
        MIN(height) AS min_height
    FROM Player
),
FilteredPlayers AS (
    SELECT
        P.player_api_id,
        P.player_name,
        AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing
    FROM Player P
    INNER JOIN Player_Attributes PA
        ON P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
    WHERE P.height BETWEEN (SELECT max_height FROM HeightRange) AND (SELECT min_height FROM HeightRange)
    GROUP BY P.player_api_id, P.player_name
)
SELECT
    player_name
FROM FilteredPlayers
WHERE avg_finishing = (SELECT MAX(avg_finishing) FROM FilteredPlayers)
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    P.player_api_id, 
    AVG(PA.finishing) AS avg_finishing_rate
FROM 
    Player P
JOIN 
    Player_Attributes PA 
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.height >= (SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player)
    AND P.height <= (SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player)
GROUP BY 
    P.player_api_id
ORDER BY 
    avg_finishing_rate DESC
LIMIT 1;

question:
What is the difference of the average ball control score between Abdou Diallo and Aaron Appindangoye
?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) -
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) AS control_difference
FROM 
    Player P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id;

SELECT 
    (SELECT AVG(pa.ball_control)
     FROM Player p
     INNER JOIN Player_Attributes pa ON p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id
     WHERE p.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo') 
    - 
    (SELECT AVG(pa.ball_control)
     FROM Player p
     INNER JOIN Player_Attributes pa ON p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id
     WHERE p.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye') AS difference_in_avg_ball_control;

SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control END) - 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control END) AS diff_avg_ball_control
FROM 
    Player P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Abdou Diallo', 'Aaron Appindangoye');

SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) -
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) AS difference
FROM 
    Player P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Abdou Diallo', 'Aaron Appindangoye');

SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) -
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) AS avg_ball_control_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id;

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P1.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA1.ball_control ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / 
     NULLIF(COUNT(CASE WHEN P1.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN 1 END), 0)) 
    - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P1.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA1.ball_control ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / 
     NULLIF(COUNT(CASE WHEN P1.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN 1 END), 0)) AS diff
FROM 
    Player AS P1
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA1
ON 
    P1.player_api_id = PA1.player_api_id;

SELECT 
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) -
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE NULL END) AS ball_control_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id;

SELECT
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control END) -
    AVG(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control END) AS avg_ball_control_difference
FROM
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE
    P.player_name IN ('Abdou Diallo', 'Aaron Appindangoye');

question: How much higher in percentage is Ariel Borysiuk's overall rating than that of Paulin Puel?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk' THEN PA.overall_rating END) - 
     MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END)) * 100.0 /
    MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Ariel Borysiuk', 'Paulin Puel');

SELECT 
    100 * (
        (SELECT overall_rating 
         FROM Player AS P1 
         JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA1 
         ON P1.player_api_id = PA1.player_api_id 
         WHERE P1.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk') 
        - 
        (SELECT overall_rating 
         FROM Player AS P2 
         JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA2 
         ON P2.player_api_id = PA2.player_api_id 
         WHERE P2.player_name = 'Paulin Puel')
    ) / 
    (SELECT overall_rating 
     FROM Player AS P3 
     JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA3 
     ON P3.player_api_id = PA3.player_api_id 
     WHERE P3.player_name = 'Paulin Puel') AS percentage_difference;

SELECT 
    (CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk' THEN PA.overall_rating END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END)
        ) AS REAL)
    ) / 
    MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END)
    ) * 100 AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Ariel Borysiuk', 'Paulin Puel');

SELECT 
    100 * (
        (SELECT overall_rating 
         FROM Player AS P1
         INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA1 
         ON P1.player_api_id = PA1.player_api_id
         WHERE P1.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk') 
        - 
        (SELECT overall_rating 
         FROM Player AS P2
         INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA2 
         ON P2.player_api_id = PA2.player_api_id
         WHERE P2.player_name = 'Paulin Puel')
    ) / 
    (SELECT overall_rating 
     FROM Player AS P3
     INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA3 
     ON P3.player_api_id = PA3.player_api_id
     WHERE P3.player_name = 'Paulin Puel') AS percentage_difference;

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk' THEN PA.overall_rating END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100 / 
    MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Paulin Puel' THEN PA.overall_rating END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Ariel Borysiuk', 'Paulin Puel');

SELECT 
    ((A.overall_rating - P.overall_rating) * 100.0 / P.overall_rating) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS Pl1
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS A
    ON Pl1.player_api_id = A.player_api_id
INNER JOIN 
    Player AS Pl2
    ON Pl2.player_api_id = A.player_api_id
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS P
    ON Pl2.player_api_id = P.player_api_id
WHERE 
    Pl1.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk'
    AND Pl2.player_name = 'Paulin Puel';

SELECT 
    100 * (
        (T2.overall_rating - T3.overall_rating) * 1.0 / T3.overall_rating
    ) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS T2
    ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
INNER JOIN 
    Player AS T4
    ON T4.player_name = 'Paulin Puel'
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS T3
    ON T4.player_api_id = T3.player_api_id
WHERE 
    T1.player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk';

SELECT 
    100.0 * (
        (T1.overall_rating - T2.overall_rating) / T2.overall_rating
    ) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    (SELECT overall_rating 
     FROM Player_Attributes 
     WHERE player_api_id = (SELECT player_api_id FROM Player WHERE player_name = 'Ariel Borysiuk')) AS T1,
    (SELECT overall_rating 
     FROM Player_Attributes 
     WHERE player_api_id = (SELECT player_api_id FROM Player WHERE player_name = 'Paulin Puel')) AS T2;

question: What is Ajax's highest chance creation passing score and what is it classified as?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    MAX(TA.chanceCreationPassing) AS max_chance_creation_passing, 
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass 
FROM 
    Team AS T 
INNER JOIN 
    Team_Attributes AS TA 
ON 
    T.team_api_id = TA.team_api_id 
WHERE 
    T.team_long_name = 'Ajax' 
GROUP BY 
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass;

SELECT 
    MAX(TA.chanceCreationPassing) AS max_chance_creation_passing,
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass
FROM 
    Team AS T
INNER JOIN 
    Team_Attributes AS TA
ON 
    T.team_api_id = TA.team_api_id
WHERE 
    T.team_long_name = 'Ajax'
GROUP BY 
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass
ORDER BY 
    max_chance_creation_passing DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    TA.chanceCreationPassing AS max_chance_creation_passing,
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass
FROM 
    Team AS T
INNER JOIN 
    Team_Attributes AS TA
ON 
    T.team_api_id = TA.team_api_id
WHERE 
    T.team_long_name = 'Ajax'
    AND TA.chanceCreationPassing = (
        SELECT MAX(chanceCreationPassing)
        FROM Team_Attributes AS TA2
        INNER JOIN Team AS T2
        ON TA2.team_api_id = T2.team_api_id
        WHERE T2.team_long_name = 'Ajax'
    );

SELECT 
    MAX(TA.chanceCreationPassing) AS max_chance_creation_passing,
    TA.chanceCreationPassingClass
FROM

WHERE

SELECT

    Team AS T
INNER JOIN 
    Team_Attributes AS TA

    T.team_api_id = TA.team_api_id
WHERE 
    T.team_long_name = 'Ajax';

-- Your SQL query
SELECT

    T2.chanceCreationPassingClass
FROM 
    Team AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    Team_Attributes AS T2
ON 
    T1.team_api_id = T2.team_api_id
WHERE 
    T1.team_long_name = 'Ajax'
    AND T2.chanceCreationPassing = (
        SELECT 
            MAX(chanceCreationPassing)
        FROM 
            Team_Attributes AS T3
        INNER JOIN 
            Team AS T4
        ON 
            T3.team_api_id = T4.team_api_id
        WHERE 
            T4.team_long_name = 'Ajax'

SELECT

    Team AS T1

    T1.team_api_id = T2.team_api_id

question: What is the average number of goals made by Parma as the away team while playing in Italy?
sql_candidates:
SELECT AVG(M.away_team_goal) AS average_goals
FROM Match AS M
INNER JOIN Team AS T
    ON M.away_team_api_id = T.team_api_id
INNER JOIN Country AS C
    ON M.country_id = C.id
WHERE T.team_long_name = 'Parma' AND C.name = 'Italy';

SELECT AVG(M.away_team_goal) AS average_goals
FROM Team AS T
INNER JOIN `Match` AS M ON T.team_api_id = M.away_team_api_id
INNER JOIN Country AS C ON M.country_id = C.id
WHERE T.team_long_name = 'Parma' AND C.name = 'Italy';

FROM Country AS C
INNER JOIN Match AS M ON C.id = M.country_id
INNER JOIN Team AS T ON M.away_team_api_id = T.team_api_id
WHERE T.team_long_name = 'Parma' AND C.name = 'Italy';

question: What percentage is Landon Donovan's overall rating higher than Jordan Bowery on 2013/7/12?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    CAST(
        (ld_donovan.rating - jb_bowery.rating) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / ld_donovan.rating AS percentage_difference
FROM (
    SELECT 
        pa.overall_rating AS rating
    FROM 
        Player_Attributes pa
    INNER JOIN 
        Player p ON pa.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
    WHERE 
        pa.date = '2013-07-12' 
        AND p.player_name = 'Landon Donovan'
) AS ld_donovan,
(
    SELECT 
        pa.overall_rating AS rating
    FROM 
        Player_Attributes pa
    INNER JOIN 
        Player p ON pa.player_api_id = p.player_api_id
    WHERE 
        pa.date = '2013-07-12' 
        AND p.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery'
) AS jb_bowery;

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (pa1.overall_rating - pa2.overall_rating) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / pa1.overall_rating AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player p1
JOIN 
    Player_Attributes pa1
    ON p1.player_api_id = pa1.player_api_id
JOIN 
    Player p2
    ON p2.player_api_id = pa2.player_api_id
JOIN 
    Player_Attributes pa2
    ON p2.player_api_id = pa2.player_api_id
WHERE 
    p1.player_name = 'Landon Donovan'
    AND p2.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery'
    AND pa1.date = '2013-07-12'
    AND pa2.date = '2013-07-12';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN PA.overall_rating END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / 
    MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    PA.date = '2013-07-12';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (PA_Landon.overall_rating - PA_Jordan.overall_rating) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / PA_Landon.overall_rating AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P_Landon
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA_Landon
    ON P_Landon.player_api_id = PA_Landon.player_api_id
INNER JOIN 
    Player AS P_Jordan
    ON P_Jordan.player_api_id = PA_Jordan.player_api_id
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA_Jordan
    ON P_Jordan.player_api_id = PA_Jordan.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P_Landon.player_name = 'Landon Donovan'
    AND P_Jordan.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery'
    AND PA_Landon.date = '2013-07-12'
    AND PA_Jordan.date = '2013-07-12';

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) - 
     CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END) AS REAL)) * 100.0 /
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    PA.date = '2013-07-12';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (donovan.rating - bowery.rating) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / donovan.rating AS percentage_difference
FROM (
    SELECT 
        pa.overall_rating AS rating
    FROM 
        Player AS p
    INNER JOIN 
        Player_Attributes AS pa
    ON 
        p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id
    WHERE 
        p.player_name = 'Landon Donovan'
        AND pa.date = '2013-07-12'
) AS donovan
CROSS JOIN (
    SELECT 
        pa.overall_rating AS rating
    FROM 
        Player AS p
    INNER JOIN 
        Player_Attributes AS pa
    ON 
        p.player_api_id = pa.player_api_id
    WHERE 
        p.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery'
        AND pa.date = '2013-07-12'
) AS bowery;

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN PA.overall_rating END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / 
    MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Landon Donovan', 'Jordan Bowery') 
    AND PA.date = '2013-07-12';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN A.overall_rating END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN A.overall_rating END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / MAX(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN A.overall_rating END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS A
ON 
    P.player_api_id = A.player_api_id
WHERE 
    A.date = '2013-07-12';

question: List down most tallest players' name.
sql_candidates:
WITH RankedPlayers AS (
    SELECT player_name, height, 
           RANK() OVER (ORDER BY height DESC) AS rank
    FROM Player
)
SELECT player_name
FROM RankedPlayers
WHERE rank = 1;

WITH PlayerRanking AS (
    SELECT 
        player_name,
        height,
        RANK() OVER (ORDER BY height DESC) AS rank
    FROM 
        Player
)
SELECT 
    player_name
FROM 
    PlayerRanking
WHERE 
    rank = 1;

question: Are there more in-patient or outpatient who were male? What is the deviation in percentage?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS Male_Inpatient_Percentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS Male_Outpatient_Percentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS Percentage_Deviation
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

-- Calculate the percentage of male in-patients and out-patients, and their difference
WITH MaleCounts AS (
    SELECT
        COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS MaleInPatients,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS MaleOutPatients,
        COUNT(*) AS TotalMalePatients
    FROM Patient
    WHERE SEX = 'M'
),
Percentages AS (
    SELECT
        MaleInPatients,
        MaleOutPatients,
        TotalMalePatients,
        (MaleInPatients * 100.0 / TotalMalePatients) AS InPatientPercentage,
        (MaleOutPatients * 100.0 / TotalMalePatients) AS OutPatientPercentage
    FROM MaleCounts
)
SELECT
    InPatientPercentage,
    OutPatientPercentage,
    ABS(InPatientPercentage - OutPatientPercentage) AS PercentageDifference
FROM Percentages;

SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
     SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 / 
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS Percentage_Deviation
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Inpatient_Count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Outpatient_Count,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / 
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS Percentage_Difference
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

(SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
      SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 /
     (SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + 
      SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Male_Inpatient_Percentage,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Male_Outpatient_Percentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS Percentage_Difference
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS InpatientCount,
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS OutpatientCount,
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS InpatientPercentage,
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS OutpatientPercentage,
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) 
        THEN (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) - 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))
        ELSE (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) - 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / 
             (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))
    END AS PercentageDifference
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID) AS Percentage_In_Patients,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID) AS Percentage_Out_Patients,
    ABS(CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID) 
        - CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(ID)) AS Percentage_Deviation
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

question: What is the ratio of male to female patients among all those with abnormal uric acid counts?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.SEX = 'M' AND T1.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) /
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.SEX = 'F' AND T1.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS Ratio
FROM 
    Laboratory AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    Patient AS T2
ON 
    T1.ID = T2.ID;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) /
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Ratio
FROM 
    Laboratory L
INNER JOIN 
    Patient P
ON 
    L.ID = P.ID;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS MaleToFemaleRatio
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE 
        WHEN P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 
        ELSE 0 
    END) AS REAL) / 
    SUM(CASE 
        WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 
        ELSE 0 
    END) AS MaleToFemaleRatio
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN L.UA <= 8.0 AND P.SEX = 'M' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) /
    SUM(CASE WHEN L.UA <= 6.5 AND P.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Ratio
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 1.0 /
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Ratio
FROM 
    Laboratory AS L
INNER JOIN 
    Patient AS P
ON 
    L.ID = P.ID;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA <= 8.0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) /
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA <= 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Ratio
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID;

question: For all patients with normal uric acid (UA), what is the average UA index based on their latest laboratory examination result?
sql_candidates:
SELECT AVG(UA) AS Average_UA
FROM (
    SELECT T2.UA
    FROM Patient AS T1
    INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID
    WHERE (T2.UA < 8.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M') OR (T2.UA < 6.5 AND T1.SEX = 'F')
    AND T2.Date = (
        SELECT MAX(T3.Date)
        FROM Laboratory AS T3
        WHERE T3.ID = T2.ID
    )
) AS Latest_Normal_UA;

-- SQL query to calculate the average UA index for patients with normal uric acid levels

FROM Laboratory AS L
INNER JOIN Patient AS P ON L.ID = P.ID

    WHERE ID = L.ID

WITH LatestLabResults AS (
    SELECT
        T1.ID,
        T1.UA,
        T1.SEX,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY T1.ID ORDER BY T1.Date DESC) AS rn
    FROM
        Laboratory AS T1
    INNER JOIN
        Patient AS T2
    ON
        T1.ID = T2.ID
)
SELECT
    AVG(UA) AS AverageUA
FROM
    LatestLabResults
WHERE
    rn = 1
    AND (UA < 8.0 AND SEX = 'M' OR UA < 6.5 AND SEX = 'F');

    SELECT ID, MAX(`Date`) AS Latest_Date

INNER JOIN Patient P ON L.ID = P.ID
WHERE (P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA < 8.0) OR (P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA < 6.5);

question: From laboratory examinations in 1991, what is the average hematoclit level that is lower than the normal range.
For patients with abnormal platelet level, state the number of patients with lower than normal range. How is it compare to the number of patients with higher than normal range?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS LowerThanNormal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS HigherThanNormal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Calculation
FROM 
    Laboratory
WHERE 
    PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Count_Lower_Than_Normal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Count_Higher_Than_Normal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Difference
FROM 
    Laboratory
WHERE 
    PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS LowerThanNormal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS HigherThanNormal,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Comparison
FROM Laboratory
WHERE PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS abnormal_platelet_difference
FROM 
    Laboratory
WHERE 
    PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS lower_than_normal_count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS higher_than_normal_count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS difference
FROM 
    Laboratory
WHERE 
    PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Platelet_Level_Difference
FROM Laboratory;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Low_PLT_Count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS High_PLT_Count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Difference
FROM

WHERE

SELECT

question: For all patients who are older than 55 years old, what is the percentage of female who has abnormal prothrombin time (PT)?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE 
        WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.PT >= 14 THEN 1 
        ELSE 0 
    END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Female_Abnormal_PT_Percentage
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID
WHERE 
    (strftime('%Y', 'now') - strftime('%Y', P.Birthday)) > 55
    AND L.PT >= 14;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS FemalePercentage
FROM 
    Patient AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory AS T2
ON 
    T1.ID = T2.ID
WHERE 
    T2.PT >= 14 
    AND strftime('%Y', 'now') - strftime('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 55;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS FemalePercentage
FROM 
    Patient AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory AS L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID
WHERE 
    (CAST(STRFTIME('%Y', current_timestamp) AS INTEGER) - CAST(STRFTIME('%Y', P.Birthday) AS INTEGER)) > 55
    AND L.PT >= 14;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' AND L.PT >= 14 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS FemalePercentage
FROM 
    Patient P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID
WHERE 
    CAST((JULIANDAY('now') - JULIANDAY(P.Birthday)) / 365.25 AS INTEGER) > 55
    AND L.PT >= 14;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS FemalePercentage
FROM 
    Patient AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory AS L
ON 
    P.ID = L.ID
WHERE 
    (CAST(strftime('%Y', current_timestamp) AS INTEGER) - CAST(strftime('%Y', P.Birthday) AS INTEGER)) > 55
    AND L.PT >= 14;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.PT >= 14 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PT >= 14 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS FemaleAbnormalPTPercentage

    Patient AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    Laboratory AS T2
ON 
    T1.ID = T2.ID
WHERE 
    CAST(strftime('%Y', 'now') AS INTEGER) - CAST(strftime('%Y', T1.Birthday) AS INTEGER) > 55;

SELECT

INNER JOIN

    T1.ID = T2.ID

    AND T2.PT >= 14;

question: Was each expense in October Meeting on October 8, 2019 approved?
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN COUNT(CASE WHEN e.approved = 'False' THEN 1 END) > 0 
        THEN 'Not all expenses were approved' 
        ELSE 'All expenses were approved' 
    END AS approval_status
FROM 
    event AS ev
INNER JOIN 
    budget AS b ON ev.event_id = b.link_to_event
INNER JOIN 
    expense AS e ON b.budget_id = e.link_to_budget
WHERE 
    ev.event_name = 'October Meeting' 
    AND ev.event_date = '2019-10-08';

    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN T3.approved = 'False' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = 0 
        THEN 'All Expenses Approved' 
        ELSE 'Not All Expenses Approved' 
    END AS approval_status
FROM 
    event AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    budget AS T2 
    ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event
INNER JOIN 
    expense AS T3

question: Among the members who incurred expenses in more than one event, who paid the most amount?
sql_candidates:
-- SQL query to find the member who paid the most amount for expenses incurred in more than one event
SELECT 
    m.first_name, 
    m.last_name, 
    SUM(e.cost) AS total_expense
FROM 
    expense e
JOIN 
    budget b ON e.link_to_budget = b.budget_id
JOIN 
    member m ON e.link_to_member = m.member_id
GROUP BY 
    e.link_to_member
HAVING 
    COUNT(DISTINCT b.link_to_event) > 1
ORDER BY 
    total_expense DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the member who paid the most amount among those with expenses in more than one event
SELECT m.first_name, m.last_name
FROM member m
JOIN (
    SELECT e.link_to_member, SUM(e.cost) AS total_spent
    FROM expense e
    JOIN budget b ON e.link_to_budget = b.budget_id
    JOIN event ev ON b.link_to_event = ev.event_id
    GROUP BY e.link_to_member
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ev.event_id) > 1
) subquery ON m.member_id = subquery.link_to_member
ORDER BY subquery.total_spent DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    m.first_name, 
    m.last_name
FROM 
    expense e
INNER JOIN 
    member m ON e.link_to_member = m.member_id
GROUP BY 
    m.member_id, m.first_name, m.last_name
HAVING 
    COUNT(DISTINCT e.link_to_event) > 1
ORDER BY 
    SUM(e.cost) DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the member who paid the most among those with expenses in more than one event
SELECT m.first_name, m.last_name
FROM (
    SELECT e.link_to_member, SUM(e.cost) AS total_cost
    FROM expense e
    INNER JOIN budget b ON e.link_to_budget = b.budget_id
    INNER JOIN event ev ON b.link_to_event = ev.event_id
    GROUP BY e.link_to_member
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ev.event_id) > 1
) sub
INNER JOIN member m ON sub.link_to_member = m.member_id
ORDER BY sub.total_cost DESC
LIMIT 1;

    T1.link_to_member

INNER JOIN 
    budget AS T2 ON T1.link_to_budget = T2.budget_id
INNER JOIN

GROUP BY

HAVING

WITH MemberExpenses AS (
    SELECT
        e.link_to_member,
        SUM(e.cost) AS total_spent,

question: Calculate the difference in the percentage of members in New Jersey and Vermont.
sql_candidates:
SELECT 
    (
        (SUM(CASE WHEN Z.state = 'New Jersey' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / COUNT(M.position = 'Member') 
        - 
        (SUM(CASE WHEN Z.state = 'Vermont' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / COUNT(M.position = 'Member')
    ) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    member AS M
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code AS Z
ON 
    M.zip = Z.zip_code
WHERE 
    M.position = 'Member';

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.state = 'New Jersey' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) 
    - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.state = 'Vermont' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS diff
FROM 
    member AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code AS T2
ON 
    T1.zip = T2.zip_code
WHERE 
    T1.position = 'Member';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN z.state = 'New Jersey' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 1.0) / 
        NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN z.state IN ('New Jersey', 'Vermont') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS REAL
    ) - 
    CAST(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN z.state = 'Vermont' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 1.0) / 
        NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN z.state IN ('New Jersey', 'Vermont') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS REAL
    ) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    member m
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code z
ON 
    m.zip = z.zip_code
WHERE 
    m.position = 'Member';

        SUM(CASE WHEN z.state = 'New Jersey' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 1.0 / COUNT(*)
        - SUM(CASE WHEN z.state = 'Vermont' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 1.0 / COUNT(*)
    ) AS state_difference
FROM 
    member m
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code z
ON 
    m.zip = z.zip_code
WHERE 
    m.position = 'Member';

FROM 
    member m
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code z
ON 
    m.zip = z.zip_code

    m.position = 'Member';

question: In 2012, who had the least consumption in LAM?
sql_candidates:
-- Final SQL Query
SELECT 
    ym.CustomerID
FROM 
    yearmonth AS ym
INNER JOIN 
    customers AS c
ON 
    ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
WHERE 
    SUBSTR(ym.Date, 1, 4) = '2012'
    AND c.Segment = 'LAM'
GROUP BY 
    ym.CustomerID
ORDER BY 
    SUM(ym.Consumption) ASC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT T1.CustomerID
FROM customers AS T1
INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
WHERE T2.Date LIKE '2012%' AND T1.Segment = 'LAM'
ORDER BY T2.Consumption ASC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the customer with the least consumption in LAM segment in 2012
SELECT T1.CustomerID
FROM customers AS T1
INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2
ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM'
  AND T2.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212'
  AND T2.Consumption = (
    SELECT MIN(Consumption)
    FROM yearmonth AS T3
    INNER JOIN customers AS T4
    ON T3.CustomerID = T4.CustomerID
    WHERE T4.Segment = 'LAM'
      AND T3.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212'
  );

SELECT T1.CustomerID
FROM customers AS T1
INNER JOIN yearmonth AS T2 ON T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
WHERE T1.Segment = 'LAM' AND T2.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201212'
GROUP BY T1.CustomerID
ORDER BY SUM(T2.Consumption) ASC
LIMIT 1;

question: What is the difference in the annual average consumption of the customers with the least amount of consumption paid in CZK for 2013 between SME and LAM, LAM and KAM, and KAM and SME?
sql_candidates:
-- SQL query to calculate the differences in annual average consumption
WITH LowestConsumers AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        MIN(y.Consumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
TotalConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
CustomerCount AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        COUNT(*) AS CustomerCount
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
AnnualAverages AS (
    SELECT 
        tc.Segment,
        tc.TotalConsumption / cc.CustomerCount AS AnnualAverage
    FROM TotalConsumption tc
    INNER JOIN CustomerCount cc ON tc.Segment = cc.Segment
)
SELECT 
    (aa_LAM.AnnualAverage - aa_KAM.AnnualAverage) AS Diff_LAM_KAM,
    (aa_KAM.AnnualAverage - aa_SME.AnnualAverage) AS Diff_KAM_SME,
    (aa_SME.AnnualAverage - aa_LAM.AnnualAverage) AS Diff_SME_LAM
FROM AnnualAverages aa_SME
INNER JOIN AnnualAverages aa_KAM ON aa_SME.Segment = 'SME' AND aa_KAM.Segment = 'KAM'
INNER JOIN AnnualAverages aa_LAM ON aa_KAM.Segment = 'KAM' AND aa_LAM.Segment = 'LAM';

WITH RankedCustomers AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        c.CustomerID,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY c.Segment ORDER BY SUM(y.Consumption) ASC) AS Rank
    FROM 
        customers c
    JOIN 
        yearmonth y
    ON 
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        c.Currency = 'CZK'
        AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
        AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY 
        c.Segment, c.CustomerID
),
LowestConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        SUM(TotalConsumption) AS TotalLowestConsumption,
        COUNT(DISTINCT CustomerID) AS NumCustomers
    FROM 
        RankedCustomers
    WHERE 
        Rank = 1
    GROUP BY 
        Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        TotalLowestConsumption / NumCustomers AS AnnualAverage
    FROM 
        LowestConsumption
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS Difference_SME_LAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS Difference_LAM_KAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') -

question: Which of the three segmentsSME, LAM and KAMhas the biggest and lowest percentage increases in consumption paid in EUR between 2012 and 2013?

WITH Consumption2012 AS (

        T1.Segment,
        SUM(T2.Consumption) AS Total2012
    FROM 
        customers AS T1
    INNER JOIN 
        yearmonth AS T2
    ON 
        T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        T2.Date LIKE '2012%' 
        AND T1.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
        AND T1.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY 
        T1.Segment
),
Consumption2013 AS (
    SELECT 
        T1.Segment,
        SUM(T2.Consumption) AS Total2013
    FROM 
        customers AS T1
    INNER JOIN 
        yearmonth AS T2
    ON 
        T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        T2.Date LIKE '2013%' 
        AND T1.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
        AND T1.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY 
        T1.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT 
        C2012.Segment,
        (C2013.Total2013 - C2012.Total2012) AS Increase,
        (C2013.Total2013 - C2012.Total2012) / C2013.Total2013 * 100.0 AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM 
        Consumption2012 AS C2012
    INNER JOIN 
        Consumption2013 AS C2013
    ON 
        C2012.Segment = C2013.Segment
)
SELECT 
    MAX(PercentageIncrease) AS MaxPercentageIncrease,
    MIN(PercentageIncrease) AS MinPercentageIncrease
FROM 
    PercentageIncrease;

WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN

        c.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'EUR'
        AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
PercentageChange AS (
    SELECT

        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) AS IncreaseDecrease,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013 AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM

)

    GROUP BY

),
CombinedData AS (

WITH ConsumptionData AS (

WITH yearly_consumption AS (

question: For the customer who paid 634.8 in 2012/8/25, what was the consumption decrease rate from Year 2012 to 2013?
sql_candidates:
WITH CustomerID AS (
    SELECT CustomerID
    FROM transactions_1k
    WHERE Amount = 634.8 AND `Date` = '2012-08-25'
),
YearlyConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        SUM(CASE WHEN `Date` LIKE '2012%' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN `Date` LIKE '2013%' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE CustomerID = (SELECT CustomerID FROM CustomerID)
)
SELECT
    (Consumption2012 - Consumption2013) * 1.0 / Consumption2012 AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate
FROM YearlyConsumption;

-- SQL query to calculate the consumption decrease rate for the specified customer
WITH CustomerID AS (
    SELECT CustomerID
    FROM transactions_1k
    WHERE Amount = 634.8 AND Date = '2012-08-25'
),
Consumption2012 AS (
    SELECT Consumption AS Consumption_2012
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE CustomerID = (SELECT CustomerID FROM CustomerID) AND Date = '201212'
),
Consumption2013 AS (
    SELECT Consumption AS Consumption_2013
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE CustomerID = (SELECT CustomerID FROM CustomerID) AND Date = '201301'
)
SELECT 
    (Consumption_2012 - Consumption_2013) / Consumption_2012 AS Consumption_Decrease_Rate
FROM 
    Consumption2012, Consumption2013;

SELECT 
    (COALESCE(Consumption_2012, 0) - COALESCE(Consumption_2013, 0)) / NULLIF(COALESCE(Consumption_2012, 0), 0) AS Consumption_Difference_Rate
FROM (
    SELECT 
        MAX(CASE WHEN `Date` LIKE '2012%' THEN Consumption ELSE NULL END) AS Consumption_2012,
        MAX(CASE WHEN `Date` LIKE '2013%' THEN Consumption ELSE NULL END) AS Consumption_2013
    FROM yearmonth
    WHERE CustomerID = (
        SELECT CustomerID
        FROM transactions_1k
        WHERE `Date` = '2012-08-25' AND Amount = 634.8
    )
) subquery;

-- SQL query to calculate the consumption decrease rate
SELECT 
    (T1.Consumption_2012 - T1.Consumption_2013) / T1.Consumption_2012 AS Consumption_Decrease_Rate
FROM (
    SELECT 
        Y1.Consumption AS Consumption_2012,
        Y2.Consumption AS Consumption_2013
    FROM yearmonth AS Y1
    JOIN yearmonth AS Y2
    ON Y1.CustomerID = Y2.CustomerID
    WHERE Y1.Date = '201208'
    AND Y2.Date = '201308'
    AND Y1.CustomerID = (
        SELECT CustomerID
        FROM transactions_1k
        WHERE Amount = 634.8
        AND Date = '2012-08-25'
    )
) AS T1;

-- Your SQL query
SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date = '2012' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - 
     SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date = '2013' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date = '2012' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate
FROM 
    yearmonth ym
WHERE 
    ym.CustomerID = (
        SELECT t.CustomerID
        FROM transactions_1k t
        WHERE t.Date = '2012-08-25' AND t.Amount = 634.8
    );

-- SQL query to calculate the consumption decrease rate
SELECT
    (consumption_2012 - consumption_2013) / consumption_2012 AS ConsumptionDecreaseRate
FROM
    (SELECT
         MAX(CASE WHEN T2.Date = '201208' THEN T2.Consumption END) AS consumption_2012,
         MAX(CASE WHEN T2.Date = '201308' THEN T2.Consumption END) AS consumption_2013
     FROM
         transactions_1k AS T1
     INNER JOIN
         yearmonth AS T2
     ON
         T1.CustomerID = T2.CustomerID
     WHERE
         T1.Amount = 634.8
         AND T1.Date = '2012-08-25') AS ConsumptionData;

    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END) = 0 THEN NULL
        ELSE 
            (SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END) - 
             SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN T2.Consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 1.0 /

    END AS Consumption_Decrease_Rate

INNER JOIN

ON

WHERE

question: Who is the top spending customer and how much is the average price per single item purchased by this customer? What currency was being used?
sql_candidates:
-- SQL query to find the top spending customer and their average price per item
WITH CustomerSpending AS (
    SELECT 
        c.CustomerID,
        SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalAmount,
        SUM(t.Price) AS TotalPrice,
        c.Currency
    FROM 
        transactions_1k t
    INNER JOIN 
        customers c
    ON 
        t.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    GROUP BY 
        c.CustomerID, c.Currency
)
SELECT 
    CustomerID,
    TotalPrice / TotalAmount AS AveragePrice,
    Currency
FROM 
    CustomerSpending
ORDER BY 
    TotalAmount DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- Step 1: Calculate total spending for each customer
WITH CustomerSpending AS (
    SELECT 
        t.CustomerID,
        SUM(t.Price) AS TotalSpent,
        SUM(t.Amount) AS TotalAmount
    FROM transactions_1k t
    GROUP BY t.CustomerID
),

-- Step 2: Identify the top spender
TopSpender AS (
    SELECT 
        CustomerID,
        TotalSpent
    FROM CustomerSpending
    ORDER BY TotalSpent DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

-- Step 3: Retrieve the currency and calculate average price per item for the top spender
SELECT 
    c.Currency,
    ts.CustomerID,
    (cs.TotalSpent / cs.TotalAmount) AS AveragePricePerItem
FROM TopSpender ts
JOIN CustomerSpending cs ON ts.CustomerID = cs.CustomerID
JOIN customers c ON ts.CustomerID = c.CustomerID;

-- SQL query to find the top spending customer, their average price per item, and their currency
WITH CustomerSpending AS (
    SELECT
        CustomerID,
        SUM(Price) AS TotalSpending,

    FROM

    GROUP BY

    ORDER BY
        TotalSpending DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
    cs.CustomerID,
    (cs.TotalSpending / cs.TotalAmount) AS AveragePricePerItem,
    c.Currency
FROM

JOIN
    customers AS c
ON
    cs.CustomerID = c.CustomerID;
